caption: Awesome atmosphere and they kept the original look of Lewis Drug store. Just the way I remembered it as a kid. The drinks were excellent and the staff very friendly.
The customer service is always prompt, great atmosphere, very friendly employees. Will return here again.

Amazing food and our waiter was very nice. However, I was so disappointed by how we were treated. We had dinner reservations at 6pm and they never told us that we would need to be finished by 7:15. They rushed out of there to seat another table The manager came over and yelled at my client. I was so embarrassed. I would love to go back, but will not due to the poor treatment.
Very flavorful, unique pasta dishes. Very interesting decor and rustic ambiance. Will be returning to try more menu items.
Excellent food at very reasonable prices. I've eaten there many times and everything is fresh and well-prepared.

Locanda & Bar Camillo have wonderful food and staff. We have done their meal kit twice. There was an honest mistake with our last meal kit having the wrong secondi, and they fixed it ASAP. They even drove us the correct secondi within minutes. And course it was delicious as always. Just an all around great reliable establishment that we always enjoy.

Love it! Always top-notch service, great drinks and wine selection and - of course - incredible food! I’ve had almost everything on the menu and never had a single dish that was anything less than phenomenal.
That place is not what it says, the cornbread was nasty,  the meat loaf had no season, it needed Bell Peppers, and ect,and the ice tea, u don't no it taste like.

Let's start with the service. I made reservations via Google and it we waited several more minutes past the time expected but not a biggie as they were packed. Once we were sat the staff were extremely helpful and pleasant. Chips and salsa were great and so were the tall Dos XX. We ordered the fajitas large, for two and It was definitely more than enough. Medium for 1-2 would have done fine if we wanted a small meal but we were hungry and the Large satisfied! Our server, Johneisha was amazing and super pleasant! Great job Locanda Vini & Olii and amazing job to John!

This takeout order was disappointing. My lasagna—which was supposed to have fresh pasta sheets, cherry tomatoes, basil, zucchini, carrots, celery, besciamella, grana padano cheese—was missing nearly all of the  ingredients. It was layers of pasta sheets (questionable if they were fresh) and some kind of cheese paste. No vegetables in sight.  The tiramisu arrived half melted from the heat of the pasta container. The chocolate cake was dry. It’s really a shame because I’ve only heard great things, but delivery is not the way to go. I would try it in person, because this restaurant has such a great reputation.
Atmosphere and food are excellent! Service was awesome!
Every time I've been there the food is delicious and the staff is fantastic. I highly recommend going for brunch.
Love this place - always good.  Especially enjoyed the Al fungi pasta tonight.  So fresh and perfectly seasoned.  Awesome onion soup too.  Friendly service and a solid outdoor setup.
Excellent food, excellent wine, excellent service
superb spot for a beer and some olives

A neighborhood gem. Super underrated. Amazing italian food with the nicest staff. We ate outdoors under the heated tent on one of the coldest nights in the pandemic and had one of the safest experiences ever. Touchless payment and safe seating. Amazing all around
Got takeout and everything was delicious! Vegan chickpea kale soup, mozz, prosciutto, and some almond cookies.
Food was very mediocre.

This is the best Italian food I’ve had in a long time. Original, simple, Northern Italian food. Ingredients are top notch and everything was super fresh. Outdoor dining was warm and accommodating. Add this place to your list!

Food was overall great. The service was mehh.  Grill duck breast was perfectly cooked, juicy meat and very delicious!  Al tartufo, black truffles pasta, sauce was on point, even though truffle slices were thiner than paper.  I wouldn’t recommend Potato gnocchi with pesto sauce which was so bland...didn’t taste anything rather than chewy gnocchi and sun dried tomato.  Two types of outdoor seatings: 1) street tables:  Under tent with a wall mounted electric heater on each table which was not enough warm on 39-45F weather...  2) Side tables with tall heaters, no barriers around. But it seemed warmer than street table since the heaters were gas heat.  If you wish to dine out, be prepared with thick coats, hats, and gloves? our hands were freezing!
Great Food.  Great service.  5* For hustling it in these tough economic times.

the place, alas, disappointed - in the photo on instagram it is beautiful, in reality it is not so)) Very long service, no one met at the entrance. min 10-15 waited for the waiter (already wanted to leave) promised 15min, brought hot in 40min.

Have had two great dinners here (once pre-pandemic and once during). The food is all delicious and the drinks are good, too! Plenty of options for vegetarians. We ate outside this time, in the sidewalk seating by a heater. Besides when there was a breeze, we were very comfortable. Definitely check it out for dinner if you’re in the area!
My favorite Italian restaurant in the city. Happy they are doing relatively well in pandemic times.

The wild boar pasta dish did not disappoint. Succulent protein and homemade tagliatelle cooked to perfection. I’d enjoy the dish at the resto with a medium bodied red next time, instead of ordering takeout.

This is very interesting place, and I am sure I will enjoy it the other time. Unfortunately, they don't serve inside (at least when I was there) and outside was rather chilling despite the heaters. So I left that place in a hurry. Although I enjoyed their food. It was simple but tasty. I really enjoyed smoked duck breast.
Good food good ambience too cold they need to shut the doors
Friendly Staff, and nice COVID outdoor setup. But most importantly great authentic Italian food! Blessed to have this place as a local establishment.
Awesome service!
For more than 15 years, the go to place in the neighborhood- an always reliable fresh pasta and delicious salad along with a beautifully paired glass of wine.  Everything on the menu here is superb!
Authentic italian food, cozy atmosphere, and great service. Especially loved the fresh maltagliati alla checca
(Translated by Google) Buffalo / pate / truffle  (Original) Bufala / patè / tartufo
Italian with creative twists. Chef is very clever. Outdoor dining was very good.
Simple, authentic Italian menu. Freshly made pasta cooked to perfection. Fig & Gorgonzola salad was perfect way to start the meal. Worth the visit!
Best tripe I’ve had in New York!  Stewed to perfection and delicious.

Came here on Saturday night. Beautiful outdoor dining with a healthy amount of space between tables at least 5 feet in each direction. All the staff were wearing masks! Bravo. The food was fantastic. We shared: prosciutto , fig salad and pappardelle ricotta pasta. Portions were large and the quality of the food was super impressive. Perhaps the most delicious pasta I have ever had! We will be back! They also have contactless pay options and all sorts of covid compliant safety measure in place, while still maintaining a casual and warm dining experience.

This charming neighborhood spot has been an icon for ages. It STILL doesn't lose its charm, even after dining here for years. The quality of ingredients expertly combined into classic (real) Italian dishes feels like getting a big, tasty hug. I absolutely love the food. The drink list is A+, with not too much selection as to paralyze one with indecision, but not too small/boring to disappoint. The adorableness of the place and its location only add to the experience. Anyone teetering on the edge of deciding to come here or not, just come. Enjoy yourself. Thanks for being here, Locanda. 🥂 Featured picture is this braised pork shank that a fork could rip apart with ease because they know how to cook.
Always a winner - simple, great Italian food; no frills but lots of love
Good
Lovely outdoor seating, quiet street, feels almost like Italy in Brooklyn. Food + cocktails are also on par.
A very unique little place with a varied menu. They were however very busy and slightly unaccommodating the day we were there. The pasta was good but not the best.
Authentic Italian cuisine in an authentic brooklyn pharmacy.  Great atmosphere and amazing foo.
Very authentic and delicious. The staff was also very attentive and nice. Will definitely come back.

Fantastic service, delicious food, cozy atmosphere, and tasty drinks. Couldn't ask for a better dining experience. Split an appetizer (venison carpacio), pasta (braised rabbit pappardelle), and entree (piedmontese flank steak) and was plenty.
The atmosphere is warm though very loud. I had a great time and a great first experience of eating rabbit.

Very hip dining experience and excellent food. Really great customer service, they were on top of things at the actual table.  Bonus Points: Called up a few days prior to make a reservation, being that I use a wheelchair, I needed to know if they had a ramp. Not only did they have a portable ramp, they had it waiting all set up prior to my reservation, attention to detail to say the least.

Love this place. From the old-school sign out front to the delicious cocktails, I am all about Locanda. Truthfully, I've only ever had drinks and apps here, but it's always a cozy, wonderful time.  Sitting at the bar is probably my favorite spot because the bartenders are friendly and very willing to offer recommendations. I usually opt for the charcuterie, but everything looks delicious. I highly, HIGHLY recommend the "soup" pappa al pomodoro (I probably butchered the actual name, but you'll get it when you see it). This soup is SO ridiculously, unbelievably good. I look at it and don't understand why it's so good, but it is. You always want more.
Decent Italian food in an intimate setting. I enjoyed their wine and grappa selection best!
Our favorite Italian place in Brooklyn. Great service, ambiance, and food. Try the olive oil!

The location was very cool, but the food left a lot to be desired. I’d recommend bringing your parents here for a relaxing evening; but if a date brought me here—let’s just say I wouldn’t call them back.

Very disappointing. Pasta with mushrooms was very oily. It ruined the mushroom and pasta flavor.Branzino was good but the onions and potatoes very oily. Chef has heavy hand with the oil. It ruined what could have been good food . Service was excellent. Overpriced for the quality a shame.

I eat in this spot a lot since I work in the area. I have to say their customer service is always great and they keep the spot neat all the time. Rates are reasonable and they serve generous portions.
What a wonderful restaurant. Exquisite food and the atmosphere, drinks, and service were all great. Do not miss the CAULIFLOWER SFORMATO over baby spinach purée with grana padano crisp. So good!

EXCELLENT! The few times I've been here I have never been disappointed by the fresh ingredients and the variety of the menu, including cocktails. Everything from the kitchen is high quality! The only minus is the tables are close and it is loud when the single room for dining is at full capacity. This only speaks to the popularity. Personally, I will opt for outside seating in front, during the warmer months. Finally, the restaurant is in a former "drug store". The signage is still on the facade. The bar has a glass countertop with vintage products displayed, as well in glass  bookcases. This is a fun element in the historical Brookly neighborhood.

The server was GREAT and the wine was good, so I can’t give it one star. By far the worst cheese plate I’ve ever had, and they seemed really confused why we would want bread with it. My friend and I each ordered a pasta and they were both awful. Mine was swimming in olive oil and didn’t taste like anything, definitely not the mushrooms the dish was named after. Hers was an overly salty meat sauce with some noodles mixed in. They were both the same brown-grey color. Needless to say, we skipped dessert.
Perfection!

Absolutely a no. We got their basil pesto pasta which was a dark brown color and tasted like Trader Joe’s pesto. Not even! But paid 25$ for it. I really don’t understand how people like this place. Pasta was overcooked and tasted less than mediocre. The location is cool for sure but the food is bad. If you’re charging that much for pasta it better be good.

We came there in a Saturday night and it was good that we had a reservation, as we learned from the couple entering before us, the wait would have been two hours. They have several different types of negronis, and since the negroni is 100 years old this year, I had to have one.It was good. Overall, dinner was an experience. The food was so delicious. The atmosphere is nice. From the outside, the building is labeled as a drug store, and the interior is decorated with drugstore paraphilia. Overall this is would be a glowing review if there would not be two areas of improvement. (1) It's really loud in there, and it's tough to carry a conversation.(2) As others have noted, the service is slow.
The CHICKEN LIVERS & TALEGGIO RISOTTO SARTU Pan-Seared in Vin Santo & fresh sage is a must!  Small, lively space.  Cool decor.
It is a odd venue... Not a destination
Very disappointing, from last time.
This was our go to until last night.  I don't know where your chef and professional waitstaff went to, but you better do whatever you need to do to get them back.  5 dishes 5 2's.
Really good tasty food. Love the home made pasta and the variety of 'aperitivi' drinks!

It's a great place to come with family. Very nice setting, excellent menu , good wine. However, I ordered ROASTED ALASKAN COD (served with roasted potatoes) which was very good but for some reason just soaked in olive oil afterwards. It was so heavily oily that my stomach started hurting, couldn't even finish the meal. When I mentioned it to our server as a comment for improvement, he just shrugged me off with "that's how we cook in Sicily". Unacceptable!

Delicious and charming! Highlights were the chicken liver starter and the venison osso bucco, one of the best entrees we've ever had. Pici, a hand-rolled spaghetti-but-fatter pasta, was much fatter and more doughy than I've had in Tuscany but the roasted onion sauce was very good. Double espresso barely filled half the thimble cup. Oh, well.Prices: Starters $10-$16, Primi (pastas) in between, and mains $25-$29. Three of us ordered two of each course and were very happy. The venue, an old drugstore, surrounds you with the dark wood and glass cabinets of another century, but it's the charm and helpfulness of the wait staff, all in lovely Italian accents, that topped the experience for me. Warning: Dark and noisy and tables are inches from each other. A lovely evening!
Excellent service and food 😀 Our 3rd visit
Enjoyed it. The food was great though I had a difficult time pronouncing the menu items. The staff is friendly.
The filling is like be home in Italy, amazing food
Every bite was amazing. We had multi course with deserts
Great food, good service, and we even made some friends there!
Great tastes, great wines, great olives, great vibes.
Nice place to visit
Incredible Italian fare with no fuss. Love the handmade pastas.
Roast duck with chick peas
Eveything was good.
My daughter surprised me by bringing  me here and we had a really good time. Food was delicious, music was fun and the ambience was  awesome.
Venison Oslo Bucco!  Do not miss this treat.

Never Again. The waiter who served  us was polite and tried probably his best, the other one(the older one) was so rude and ignorant with my daughter that ruined our birthday celebration.Food was nothing special to be mentioned, but this is just my 50¢ review as 100% Italian  I might be too much picky..
As good and authentic as any meal we had in Italy.
The best restaurant in the neighborhood hands down. Fantastic food, great atmosphere and good people. Great for an event as well.
Great location and delicious food; the only downside is the space can be a bit tight.  A really broad selection,  a lot of seafood, fresh and creative.
A very bustling Tuscan-inspired restaurant. Great atmosphere and delicious Italian food. Located in an old drugstore!

Im suprised to read all these nice reviews about the food. Amazing location no doubt, but I got the rabbit pappardelle. There were bones in it and it tasted terrible.  I couldn't finish more than a few bits. If you are charging the prices they're charging, you better make something better.
It is a nice place for a grown-up dining experience or date night. It is not children friendly
The food was actually very tasty. My first time going and it is cute and intimate.
A very special place. Great ambiance and wonderful food.
Solids Italian option in Clinton hill
Great table wine, very pretty setting, good food
Lovely restaurant with great service
Absolutely amazing pasta! Our waiter knew the ins and outs of the food, wine, and cocktails. All of which were amazing. Honestly the best Italian food I've had in Brooklyn.

A neighborhood Italian restaurant in a former drug store. They boast of exceptional olive oil collection,  a sizable Italian and California wine collection.  The dishes are great tasting and the portions are satisfying. An excellent and friendly staff. Good all around.
Was there tonight for a wine dinner event.  Food was spectacular, wine was interesting and new!  Highly recommended.

Went to Locanda Vini & Olii last night with my husband and another couple and had a wondering evening. The food was delicious and we all enjoyed trying flavor combinations that were new to us; nice portion sizes. The ambiance is great, but above all - it's the staff who make this place extra special. They are so genuine and kind, there is no wonder why this establishment is so authentic. We live in Manhattan, but they've won us over, worth the subway ride.
Really cute and delicious pasta!
One of the best places to eat in Brooklyn. Get the livers. Perfect for a date or a group dinner. You just can't go wrong.
Solid date spot. Cute menus. Duck was ok. Pesto gnocchi was good. Ancient soup was pretty tasty. Would go w the beef next time

Enjoyed the chef’s tasting menu with friends and was overwhelmed by the amount of food. Definitely filling with some dishes really shining: sage mushroom pasta, rabbit ragú pappardelle, calamari in tomato appetizer, and the ricotta cheesecake is not to be missed.
Food was delicious. True Italian!

A wonderful experience. The staff and food make this a find. We ordered the tasting menu and had great fun. Highly recommend the exceptional olives, pasta with the boar meat,  pasta with pancetta, branzino and rabbit. The deserts were fantastic!

Will not go back. Duck was done properly but chickpeas had no flavor and just bunched on plate like out of the can. Gnocci was awful tasted like it was made totally from flour and swimming in heavy oliveoil and basil, no flavor at all! The three shrimp that came with the dish were overcooked and very fishy smelling. I asked for a cosmopolitan cocktail and had a mystery drink which was taken back. This place is overpriced, dishes have no flavor, bland bland bland and I cannot belive this is a good representation of Tuscan food. Real Tuscan food is at hidden away at “VINUM” on Bay Street in Staten Island. Organic, flavorful and delicious! Worth the trip!

I’ve been going to Locanda for 15 years, and it has been amazing every time. Hey Best staff, environment and food; combined with great service and consistency. Can’t get better than that! So far best restaurant in Bk
Fabulous NYE dinner. Will be returning shortly!

Wonderful food in a converted old drug store with lots of charm. Feels like an apothecary shop, with the glass cabinets and sliding ladders that now serve as coat racks. Prix fixe New Year's Eve menu was fresh and delicious, especially the gnocchi with pesto. Great cocktails, wine, and dessert, too.
Great food , amazing service in a beautiful intimate setup

The drinks and server was fantastic. The food was however one of the worst meals I've ever had. More so, only having one meal that day and getting food poisoining wasn't on my itinerary either. Really sad state of affairs. Wish I could refund my entire meal.
Amazing food. Decent prices. But very loud and slow service

I had high hopes after just moving to the neighborhood but was disappointed in food and service. Servers were abrupt, inattentive and unhelpful. The stewed calamari sauce tasted like salty anchovy liquid and worse with very overstewed squid. The pastas were slightly better in that the pasta tasted fresh. However the sauces of the Buttera pasta and the pappardelle lacked flavour with no taste of sage as the menu said and was oversalted. Too many good Italian options to go back.
My neighborhood favorite place.
What a cool place! I'm almost inclined to say nothing in the hopes that it stays as quiet as it is!! Great ambiance, delicious food, and great service!

I was delighted to find this place in our neighborhood. One of the best Italian restaurants I’ve ever eaten in, and that includes Italy! A bit pricey and loud , but the staff is outgoing and extremely helpful (we’re vegan) and the house made wines are really good. We’re on our way back.
Yum!!!!Italian food like it should be, authentic to it's region, well done and with less fuss.
More Florentine than many a restaurant in Florence.     Worth a trip.
Such a great vibe and amazing food
Very cool atmosphere, great food. They make an amazing old fashioned cocktail
Amazing authentic Italian. Very slow service
Everything was just perfect. The steak explodes with flavor inside your mouth.
Amazing service and delicious food in a very cool setting.
Delicious

Delicious, warm Italian food in a relaxed, unfussy atmosphere. Ask to be seated outside if the weather permits.  Our table of two was indulgent with the antipasti, ordering the panzanella and campagna meat board (enough for four to share). The panzanella was refreshing, acidic, and featured cukes with a crisp bite. Highlights from the meat board were a generous serving of fatty prosciutto and a delightful pheasant terrine dotted with sweet green grapes.  Besides that, we shared the wild boar pappardelle, Alaskan cod garnished with a savory-sweet butter sauce and sliced fried potatoes, and duck breast with a surprising but welcoming side of warm fig jam and steamed chickpeas.  No room for dessert. Perhaps next time.

Voted Best Italian in New York. Hand made pasta & bread. House olive oil for purchase... makes a great gift! Wines by the bottle are listed on actual bottles, also great by the glass list. Try the orange wine, named for the color. The duck beast is the reason I'm going back asap. Reservations not required, but recommended.

Went here recently with some friends. The food quality was very good. Definitely on the pricier side though so not very budget friendly, for that it is a great once in a while place.  We got a fixed menu for 4. The server brought out multiple dishes chosen by the chef.  Would return
Great Italian restaurant in Clinton Hill, fantastic menu and setting to dine in. Small space so it fills fast.

A wonderful restaurant for a special night! We loved the ambiance, the food, and the drink selection! We ate the mozzarella appetizer, spaghetti with red sauce and pancetta, and cod with potatoes, and all were so delicious. I look forward to going back sometime soon!
Awesome place

Very good food. I had the risotto with chicken livers & gravy, it was wonderful! Also had the chicken with potatoes, chicken seemed a little overcooked & dry. Had chocolate & rum gelato that was delightful. A wonderful evening spent with my daughter's best friend Michael whom I hadn't seen in a year & delicious dinner!
Awesome meal. So glad I've been introduced to this place! Will definitely be back!
Fine phood in an old farmacy, great vibes & vine.
Warm and friendly service and amazing food. My favorite restaurant in Brooklyn.
Cozy restaurant for a great Italian meal

This was our second experience here. It was excellent 2 years ago, but last night was really awesome. The food tasted outstanding, was hot,  and the service was top notch. If we didn't live so far away we would eat here quite often. Best place in NY City.
One of the best Italian places in NYC. The wine selection is outstanding.
Great Italian food and wines. I enjoy their dishes every time I go there. Dinner only.

Delicious Italian restaurant in a cosy, yet cool setting. We had to change our reservation about three times on a busy Saturday night to accommodate friends, and each time, the staff we gracious and welcoming. We sat inside, and I loved the ambience. The service, right from the time we sat down, to the bringing of the cheque, was great - our glasses were never empty and neither was our table of food. The food was perfect - portion sizes were perfect to share, and we enjoyed each of our courses. We ordered the house wine, and found that it perfectly complimented each of the dishes we had. Love this place.
Some of the best, well prepared Italian meals I've had in the city. Quality cocktail menu as well. With seating both inside and out there are lots of ways to enjoy this restaurant.
Great food, amazing service, awesome atmosphere! Worth the drive to Brooklyn!
Incredible meal with a great atmosphere and friendly staff. Would highly recommend, we did the full three courses and loved each of them.
Great food. Great service.
Excellent, as always. Unfortunately I only took pictures of the dessert, but the pasta was perfectly cooked, and the sauces sublime. Well-worth the detour.

Best Italian restaurant in the city in my opinion including all the over-hyped places in Manhattan. Their steak, duck mains and mushroom, white truffle pasta are amazing. Menu changes all the time. Service is awesome and everyone is so enthusiastic!

10/10 on ambiance and amazing appetizers. I'm not a foodie but the food was very high quality and had pleanty of hip things to try along with some traditional dishes. I didn't see the steak on the menu but someone was eating it and it looked bomb and like the prefect proportions.
This place is exceptional.  Old pharmacy turned into a great Italian restaurant.  Prices are reasonable and the food was outstanding. Perfect experience.

Amazing. Authentic Italian food in a really charming setting with warm and attentive service. We started with a gin & grapefruit cocktail and a specialty artichoke negroni. Both delightful. The chicken liver and the cauliflower antipasto were both excellent. I don't love liver, but hubby convinced me to try his and I must admit it was rich and silky. The tartufo & white asparagus primi was outstanding - it is hard not to love a truffle, and the homemade pasta was perfection. The lamb "casserole" was tender, flavorful, had just the right mix of meat and veg, and was not at all gamey. A scoop of house-made lemon basil gelato  (so refreshing) and chocolate orange (decadent) sealed the deal. Bravo!!!
One of Brooklyn best restaurant

Love this place for a date or when parents are in town. Great, friendly service and cozy interior. Haven't tried many entrees because I always over order on the appetizers and pasta but the branzino is fantastic. Looks like a pharmacy from the outside but actually a great little neighborhood restaurant on the inside.
Really impressive Italian menu. Food's so good.

One of the local favorites. Phenomenal food, great service. Campagna plate is very filling for anyone considering it as an appetizer to share - it was a bit much for us two, but very delicious. Duck entree was fantastic. Really fun atmosphere, albeit a bit loud on a Saturday night.

Excellent neighborhood spot with authentic cuisine that never fails to excite and satisfy.  The tasting menu is an incredible value,  and provides the opportunity to experience the breadth of talent in the kitchen.  Hospitality  is pitch-perfect,  evoking the sophistication of fine- dining and the comfort of familiarity.  Best restaurant in Clinton Hill,  bar-none.
Seriously hospitable restaurant that takes its Italian food seriously
Love this place! Food is great and the staff a delight!
Variable food but a good neighborhood family spot
An experience!
Authentic old-shool Italian at its best.
Was in Italy this past summer.  This local bistro reminded me of the wonderful restaurants I experienced there.  Authentic and delicious.
This is the best Italian restaurant in New York.
Food is decent, certainly unworthy of the price tag or menu. Decor is also in need of some reworking. Cute items, but not exactly what I want to be surrounded by while eating.
Authentic Italian food!!!

Yummy different/authentic Italian food. This place is a renovated drug store that dates back from the 1800's. The dishes are small but filling, beautifully crafted and full of flavor. Save room for dessert because they are all delicious I recommend sharing. They still have the old ladder that goes around the entire restaurant on a track.
The food was good and very familiar place
Excellent every time there's simply no better way to put it.
This cozy place really feels like you're in Tuscany, and the food tastes like it too. Save yourself an expensive plane ticket to Florence, come here instead!
Great ambience, well-devised and prepared food, interesting wine, informed service. The drugstore look is fun.
The food is good
love this place, real neighborhood gem, great vibe, good food
Unique service, atmosphere and food. Love this place!

The location is really unique, in an old pharmacy that hasn't been stripped from it's original interior. Yet, I have been coming here for years, and it's still the same menu of unfortunately pretty basic "Italian style" food. Most of the dishes are very heavy and not presented in the most creative way. Especially for the money. Wine list is really good though and the service very friendly.
Delicious Italian food. Get the truffle pasta but only in the winter, in the summer they seemed to not have the good truffles in stock.

I came here with a friend for dinner. This used to be an old apothecary and all the woodwork is the same, the small little drawers and the ladders. They also kept all the items they found during the renovations under the front counter as well as the old register.  The food is northern Italian and I had the gnocchi with mussels, my friend had the duck. I would recommend both, I think I liked the duck more, but it really just depends on the mood you are in. They make good recommendations for the wine as well.  The service was really good, they were not constantly hovering but made sure wine and water glasses were filled. The manager Rocco came over and spoke to us as well, friendly person, and very involved in the restaurant activities.  It's good for a date night but make reservations. Also the sign on the top is the old drug store sign so don't get thrown by that.
Really fantastic Italian food. Definitely experiment with bread and olive oil there in addition to the fantastic menu.
(Translated by Google) Pazzeschi homemade pasta with flour and water from Italy  (Original) Pazzeschi pasta fatta in casa con farina e acqua dall'Italia
Food spectacular  ,people  soon nice atmosphere awesome I love it
Good food nice building and good service.

This place gets a lot of hype, but it feels misplaced.  Have been twice, both times the food was a little disappointing given the price (relative to the less expenses Aita nearby, which I also find tastier).  As well, we found the service to be a little dismissive and slow both time.  While the decor is pretty cool as an old pharmacy, it is VERY tight and fairly loud.  You wont be offended going here but I think there are better options!
A neighborhood landmark. The best. Great date spot. Friendly staff. Amazing food.
Always love it here, great Italian wine list, taglierinni with truffles was the most amazing pasta dish I've had in years.  Wild boar pappardelle was magnificent as well.

Birthday dinner for my partner was fabulous from start to finish: incredible fresh pasta, salads, superb branzino in parchment with fennel, and light, airy chocolate cake -- the staff even remembered it was his birthday from my reservation and brought it in with a candle. We will be back!
My favorite restaurant in NYC!
Imaginative Italian menu in authentic residential Brooklyn neighborhood.

Great Italian spot to try a couple of dishes that are not in your everyday Italian restaurant's menu. Charming interior and architectural history. If it's a nice day out, sitting outside is great since it's on such a beautiful block.
Amazing is the only proper way to describe this place. The food lights up my tongue's pallet like a techno-colored keyboard.
The peach nectar spritz is really great. Our pastas were very delicious
Amazing food and service. The perfect neighborhood spot for special dinners.
We came in without a reservation on a busy Saturday night and they were very kind to seat us anyways. The food was delicious and the staff was very friendly

Always wonderful no matter what night you dine.  We try to go as much as we can living in Suffolk County!!  Saturdays are wonderful...You are not rushed by any means.  If you closed your eyes you would think you were in Tuscany in a local restaurant.  Chef Baldacci, Rocco, Michael and Gabriel are truly amazing....Bravo!

Lovely, homey little place. Great service. Clever winelist-on-three-bottled schtick.  The food was atypical, which once you've been to enough Italian restaurants is not something you ever expect to see again. And it was good. But it wasn't great. Love this place for the way it makes Italian food that is more reminiscent of the Mediterranean coast of Italy rather than the normal Italian American food you get in the rest of brooklyn. Great atmosphere but the food left me wanting more. I had the papperdelle pasta with braised rabbit, it was good but I was hoping for more. Love this place. The service is excellent, the food is divine, and there's not a hint of pretense.

Romantic place with a charm. Make a reservation beforehand, it gets busy! Truly reminds me of a trattoria in Italy. Wine is delicious, food has a home cooked feel. Great place for a special occasion, it's $$$. We ordered the seared duck with chickpeas and fig jam, piche pasta with caramelized onions, white asparagus with baratta cheese. All very delicious. The house wine is pretty good and they have a funny measuring system - you pour as much as you need and they charge by measuring the amount consumed using a stick. Very unique place. Service was amazing. Everyone makes you feel at home. Also very intimate dining, we had fun convos with our neighbors.

The food and service was great. We got the family style chef menu and they made sure to make the dishes fit the preferred mood of the table. Definitely come with a appetite, they bring out a lot of food for the money.

One of the best meals I've had in a while. Came with my wife for her birthday and had a great time. Some beautiful cocktails and a fantastic 3 course meal. Great and knowledgeable staff. Highly recommended.

Really nice place, love the old pharmacy look. Eggless pasta and steak are delicious. They also know their wines.

You'll feel like you're dining in Italy. If Italy were in a beautiful, vintage Brooklyn pharmacy. The space is filled with the original pharmacy cabinets and lots of food memorabilia. They serve really delicious, no-nonsense, rustic Italian food that tasted like someone's grandmother cooked for you. Its bustling service wise. My favorite dishes were the cauliflower souffle, the sardines, the short ribs, and the duck ragu pappardelle. But everything was good.

I really enjoyed my meal at Locanda Vini & Olli. The food was excellent, the house wine was just right, and the service was friendly and quick. The atmosphere of this place is pretty cool with a lot of old pharmacy stuff all about, giving it an extra level of awesomeness.

While cute and gets great reviews - the food was just not good. The simple apps of burrata and fig/Gorgonzola salad were delish, but the main courses ranged from so so to bad. The duck was great but the chickpeas were bland and looked and tasted as if they were drained from a can and unappetizingly piled on a plate. The seafood stew lacked flavor and every piece of seafood was terribly overcooked. The eggplant pasta was just plain bad. Guess they were having an off night - but cost the same nonetheless.

One of my Brooklyn favorites, this is a phenomenal neighborhood spot that offers insanely delicious italian at affordable pricing. Few places in the neighborhood, or the entire city, for that matter, offer the kind of atmosphere that this old pharmacy turned italian eatery offer. The staff is great and knowledgeable and there is even a bar to sit at and sip cocktails if you aren't hungry.

In an old drugstore complete with candyman ladder! Super simple and delicious. I love the carrot tagliatele and saffron chitara with sardines and golden raisins.
